      <title>Re: Monks</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&amp;message.id=10756#M10756</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;Broken...  This term is poorly defined.  Broken in the developer's eyes is if you hit FD and warp to Freeport sewers.  I would like to broaden that definition and say that broken is - adding little or no value to the monk class.  Some examples follow:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;1.  Special attacks - do little or no damage in today's game.  This cannot be intended.  Why not make them truly &amp;quot;special&amp;quot;?  Let us get tombs that increase our FK damage, or scale it with some skill that continues to increase.  Don't be content to leave our special attacks in their current form.  They bring no value to the monk class.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;2.  Discs - when was the last time you even looked at your discs.  We have innerflame/speedfocus and that's it for DPS.  Ashenhand and Thunderkick?  Please...  And why link them at all?  Does this control our massive damage?  I think not.  Again, no value in linking, few to choose from.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;3.  Pulling - it used to be you needed a puller to survive, and a monk was the first choice.  No more.  I have seen a mage pull a named out from under a dozen mobs in literally 2 seconds, while I struggle like mad to split that same group.  Why can we monkey lull one at a time?  Why not 2 or 3 even?  Would it then be too easy?  No value in single lull.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;4.  Itemization - Why are my weapons the same or worse in ratio that some other classes?  Monks should have a CLEAR weapon advantage, and there should be plenty to choose from at all levels of the game.  I still use a REBB while waiting for something else to drop.  And is there value in making thing weigh 2 stones or more???  Please.  Just stop.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;5.  Usefullness - I sometimes feel like an old rusty weapon.  Not as sharp as it used to be.  Too heavy to wield in today's battlefield.  I have no group utility, and if I can't pull I have very little use.  DPS is behind, tanking is non-existant, and utility is not part of our definition.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font size="2"&gt;Lets jazz things up a bit.  We are still fun to play...  that is when I actually get a group.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
